at the moment there is just the possibility to configure givenName and surname in atlassian-user.xml. There's no chance to have a <displaynameAttribute> to map to confluence full name used everythere in the wiki.

Background is that we have coworkers with first and middle name in the givenName. But the coworkers doesn't want to "persent" all their given + middle names and we don't want to change the long givenName for other reasons. The "short" version is saved in the displayName attribute. So i'd would be fine just to map the displayName to confluence's internal full name and not to use given and surname in combination. So a <displaynameAttribute> in atlassian-user.xml is great.

