This is useful when a developer needs to exclude whole browser-specific JS files. For instance, excanvas.js (a canvas emulator for Internet Explorer). Excluding that would reduce the download time for users of other browsers.

It would be nice if this can be done with a parameter in the plugin's descriptor.

Use the following markup:

{noformat}{pagetree:root=<script>alert('12')</script>}{noformat}


Whenever the page is viewed, the script will be executed.

